<subSubSection id="ADBF95F9FFB4FF8707AAFC6FFB2CFB01" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph id="E51AC672FFB4FF8707AAFC6FFA93FC29" blockId="7.[151,1437,870,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
AZ: Cochise County, Huachuca Mountains, Sierra Vista; 
<date id="911BE0B2FFB4FF87041EFC6FFC14FC61" box="[803,953,907,933]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2010-08">August 2010</date>
; A. V. Evans. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF87039DFC6FFA91FC61" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1901" box="[1184,1340,907,933]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF87039DFC6FFA91FC61" box="[1184,1340,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aphonopelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF87025EFC6FFE3EFC0D" authority="Chamberlin" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1940" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcodes">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF87025EFC6FFEABFC0D" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">chalcodes</emphasis>
Chamberlin
</taxonomicName>
(Desert blond tarantula) (
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF870586FC4BFCCBFC0E" box="[699,870,943,970]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Theraphosidae</taxonomicName>
), adult female. The wasp examined the paralyzed tarantula with her mouthparts and antennae as it laid dorsal side upward on the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="8134BB83FFB4FF8703A1FC37FA9EFC29" author="Evans, A. V." box="[1180,1331,979,1005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref77913" refString="Evans, A. V. (2010 a) Tarantula vs. Tarantula Hawk. Available from: https: // arthurevans. wordpress. com / 2010 / 09 / 15 / tarantula-vstarantula-hawk / (accessed 15 May 2017)" type="url" year="2010">Evans 2010a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51AC672FFB4FF8707AAFC13FB1FFB9E" blockId="7.[151,1437,870,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
AZ: Maricopa County, Mesa; 
<date id="911BE0B2FFB4FF8706DEFC13FDDFFBD5" box="[483,626,1015,1041]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2016-04-09">
9 
<bibRefCitation id="8134BB83FFB4FF8706C8FC13FDDFFBD5" author="April" box="[501,626,1015,1041]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref70154" refString="April (2016)  tarantulahawk  southernutah. Available from: https: // www. instagram. com / p / BMy 2 pyfjxs 2 /? takenby = glowinggoby (accessed 5 June 2018)" type="url" year="2016">April 2016</bibRefCitation>
</date>
; B. Korb. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF87041EFC13FC12FBD5" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1901" box="[803,959,1015,1041]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF87041EFC13FC12FBD5" box="[803,959,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aphonopelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf 
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF8704DDFC13FBFAFBD5" box="[992,1111,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF8704DDFC13FBFEFBD5" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1940" box="[992,1107,1015,1041]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcodes">chalcodes</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
immature. The wasp grasped the paralyzed tarantula by the base of its right foreleg with her mandibles and pulled it backwards on the ground. She dragged the spider for a distance of about 
<quantity id="225D6B97FFB4FF8705F3FBDBFD56FB9D" box="[718,763,1087,1113]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="2.0">2 m</quantity>
, climbing through a bush (
<bibRefCitation id="8134BB83FFB4FF87031BFBDBFB0BFB9E" author="Korb, B." box="[1062,1190,1087,1114]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref83583" refString="Korb, B. (2016) Tarantula Hawk dragging prey- Pepsis - female. Available from: http: // www. bugguide. net / node / view / 1223095 / bgimage (accessed 3 May 2017)" type="url" year="2016">Korb 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51AC672FFB4FF8707AAFB87FB2CFB01" blockId="7.[151,1437,870,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
AZ: Pima County, Sabino Canyon National Park; 
<date id="911BE0B2FFB4FF8705EBFB87FCD4FBB9" box="[726,889,1122,1149]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2015-04-28">28 April 2015</date>
; R. C. Clark. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF87035FFB87FB53FBB9" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1901" box="[1122,1278,1123,1149]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF87035FFB87FB53FBB9" box="[1122,1278,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aphonopelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF870218FB87FA38FBB9" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1940" box="[1317,1429,1123,1149]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcodes">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF870218FB87FA38FBB9" box="[1317,1429,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">chalcodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, immature female. The wasp grasped the paralyzed tarantula by the base of its right pedipalp or foreleg with her mandibles and dragged it backwards on the ground, dorsal side upward (
<bibRefCitation id="8134BB83FFB4FF8704CCFB4FFBDBFB01" author="Clark, R. C." box="[1009,1142,1194,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref74506" refString="Clark, R. C. (2015) &quot; Life and death in the desert. &quot; Available from: https: // www. flickr. com / photos / dancingsnakenaturephotography / 19554788733 / (accessed 10 July 2017)" type="url" year="2015">Clark 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="ADBF95F9FFB4FF8707AAFB2BFD37F995" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E51AC672FFB4FF8707AAFB2BFCBCFAF5" blockId="7.[151,1437,870,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
AZ: Pima County, Tucson, Tohono Chul Park; 
<date id="911BE0B2FFB4FF87059AFB2BFC83FB2D" box="[679,814,1230,1257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2015-07-01">1 July 2015</date>
; G. Spesard. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF87033AFB2BFB0EFB2D" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1901" box="[1031,1187,1231,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF87033AFB2BFB0EFB2D" box="[1031,1187,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aphonopelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF8703FAFB2BFA9AFB2D" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1940" box="[1223,1335,1231,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcodes">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF8703FAFB2BFA9AFB2D" box="[1223,1335,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">chalcodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, adult or subadult female. The wasp grasped the paralyzed tarantula by the base of its 2 
<superScript id="12D06B3AFFB4FF87031CFB16FB9CFAC4" attach="left" box="[1057,1073,1266,1280]" fontSize="6" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">nd</superScript>
right leg with her mandibles and dragged it backwards on the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="8134BB83FFB4FF87055BFAF3FCA8FAF5" author="Spesard, G." box="[614,773,1302,1329]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref97192" refString="Spesard, G. (2015) A providing mother. Available from: https: // www. flickr. com / photos / arizona _ native / 18713484844 / in / album- 72157625109336807 / (accessed 19 May 2017)" type="url" year="2015">Spesard 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51AC672FFB4FF8707AAFADFFE46FA21" blockId="7.[151,1437,870,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
AZ: Pinal County, Apache Junction; 
<date id="911BE0B2FFB4FF870508FADFFD6DFA91" box="[565,704,1339,1365]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2012-06-01">1 June 2012</date>
; C. Brown. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF8704B6FADFFB8AFA91" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1901" box="[907,1063,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF8704B6FADFFB8AFA91" box="[907,1063,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aphonopelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF870376FADFFB16FA91" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1940" box="[1099,1211,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcodes">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF870376FADFFB16FA91" box="[1099,1211,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">chalcodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, adult female. After stinging and paralyzing the tarantula, the wasp tried unsuccessfully to pull the much larger and heavier spider backwards by grasping its spinnerets with her mandibles. Probably because of its relatively large size and heavy weight the tarantula was only lightly paralyzed and moved its legs frequently while lying dorsal side upward on the ground (
<bibRefCitation id="8134BB83FFB4FF870670FA2FFE72FA21" author="Brown, C." box="[333,479,1483,1509]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref72794" refString="Brown, C. (2012) Tarantula Hawk Wasp Vs Tarantula. Available from: https: // www. youtube. com / watch? v = 287 mfv 6 lbDU (accessed 27 May 2017)" type="url" year="2012">Brown 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E51AC672FFB4FF8707AAFA0BFD37F995" blockId="7.[151,1437,870,2014]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
AZ: Pinal County, Superstition Mountains; 
<date id="911BE0B2FFB4FF8705B5FA0BFC84F9CD" box="[648,809,1519,1545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2013-04-21">21 April 2013</date>
; C. Brown. Host: 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF8704C7FA0BFB3BF9CD" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1901" box="[1018,1174,1519,1545]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF8704C7FA0BFB3BF9CD" box="[1018,1174,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Aphonopelma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cf 
<taxonomicName id="22A5BDF1FFB4FF870380FA0BFA80F9CD" authorityName="Chamberlin" authorityYear="1940" box="[1213,1325,1519,1545]" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Aphonopelma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chalcodes">
<emphasis id="D7D11A60FFB4FF870380FA0BFA80F9CD" box="[1213,1325,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">chalcodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, adult female. The wasp pulled the paralyzed tarantula backwards on the ground, dorsal side upward, grasping its chelicerae with her mandibles (
<bibRefCitation id="8134BB83FFB4FF8706C0F9D3FD22F995" author="Brown, C." box="[509,655,1591,1617]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refId="ref72833" refString="Brown, C. (2013) Another Tarantula Hawk Wasp vs Tarantula. Available from: https: // www. youtube. com / watch? v = CF 55 JhncQ Ow &amp; t = 1885 (accessed 25 August 2017)" type="url" year="2013">Brown 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
